RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6F Turf CR: 103. Starter Allowance Purse 50000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 23 Allowed 2 lbs. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JETOVATOR tossed his head and got bumped leaving the gate, stalked in hand early, bid two wide around the turn, took over at the top of the stretch, inched ahead from TOOK CHARGE, maintained a short lead into deep stretch and lasted in the closing moments. REDLINE raced at the back on the inside, tipped two wide exiting the bend, moved out further at the top of the stretch, closed late three deep but could not get by the winner. SOUTHERN HORSE (ARG) unhurried in the beginning, raced outside a rival and two wide into and around the bend, steered out in upper stretch, launched a late bid and got edged for the place honors four deep at the wire. TOOK CHARGE bumped with JETOVATOR at the start, cleared and crossed over, challenged by that same rival around the turn, relinquished the lead at the top of the stretch, fought back from inside through the lane and stayed on to the wire while getting outfinished. CREW DRAGON tracked off the rail then outside a rival, rounded the bend two wide and finished willingly while needing to find that needed late kick. COMMANDER (FR) settled inside, coaxed along through the turn and flattened in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Jetovator
ENTRY.OWNER: Ciaglia Racing LLC and SAF Racing
ENTRY.COMMENT: threw head/bumped start, in hand, bid 2wide, inched ahead, lasted

RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIRASANA broke alertly from outside, pressed the pace up the backstretch, took over past the three-eighths pole, put away APPLE FEST approaching the quarter pole, roused at the top of the lane and widened when flagged with the whip, then coasted in nearing the wire. CONQUISTAR settled off the pace, entered the turn two wide, coaxed around the bend then had to pause when trying to go between runners near the five-sixteenths pole, angled four wide into the stretch and finished willingly to best the rest. RUBY NELL stalked the top pair up the backstretch, ridden along from the rail then two wide into the stretch and could not produce a bid. APPLE FEST went up to take control and set the pace with VIRASANA to the outside, was overtaken by that rival past the three-eighths pole, could not keep up with that rival with a quarter mile left to run and faded in the lane. COLLECTMYTHOUGHTS was off slow and bumped in the beginning, moved into range off the rail, took the turn three wide and weakened. DUCHESSOFBAYRIDGE bumped with inner rival at the start, raced greenly while reserved early, saved ground through the turn, came out in upper stretch and failed to menace.

By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, April 13, 2023, closed with 12 or by Supplementary nomination of $2,000 due at time of entry. $750 to enter and an additional $750 to start with $100, 000 guaranteed of which $60,000 to the winner, $20,000 to second, $12,000 to third, $6,000 to fourth and $2,000 to fifth. 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of Two races other than Maiden, Claiming or Starter allowed 4 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHATMAKESSAMMYRUN bobbled and broke in a bit leaving the gate, tracked two wide in hand at the back into the turn, angled widest across the dirt to launch a bid five deep, dueled with AIR FORCE RED in the final sixteenth and dug in to edge the runner-up. AIR FORCE RED stalked the pace two wide into the turn, bid from outside around the bend and three wide into the stretch, bumped at the three-sixteenths pole, fought through the lane and carried a narrow lead into deep stretch, dueled to the wire but was edged in the closing moments. INDIAN PEAK was off a bit slow in the beginning, stalked along the rail, launched a bid from the fence in upper stretch, reached the front at the eighth pole but faltered in deep stretch. BURNIN TURF got put in a bit tight early next to the outer rail, tracked three wide around the turn, put in mild bid four wide entering the stretch but flattened in the late stages. SUNRISE JOURNEY broke well to establish the front quickly, showed the way along the inside into the turn, got pressured by AIR FORCE RED around the bend, dueled two wide into the lane and bumped with that rival at the three-sixteenths pole, lost command in upper stretch and weakened in the furlong grounds.

TIMELY LUCK tracked outside a rival early, asked three then four wide on the far turn, drew alongside the winner in upper stretch, kept the pressure on through the final furlong while drifting out some and could not get by. IDESSIA broke a step slow then settled inside, ridden along while steered off the rail to entered the stretch three wide, finished well in the furlong grounds and but ran out of time. CANDY ON TOP moved inside and took a stalking position, tipped two wide at the quarter pole, stayed within striking in the lane but finished evenly late. BETSY IS THE CODE was off slow in the beginning, raced two wide near the back, saved ground on the far turn, tipped out in upper stretch and lacked a bid. ELA CALIMERA MOU stumbled leaving the gate, trailed on the inside into the first turn, went outside a rival in the two path on the second bend and improved position. YVETT'S SURPRISE raced three then two wide around the first turn off the pace, had to steady approaching the half-mile pole, went two wide into the far turn, four wide into the lane and failed to rally. TAPIT ROCKS raced two wide at the back outside a rival, moved closer three deep on the far turn, moved out around the bend and came six wide into the stretch and weakened. PALACSINTA dueled from outside into the first turn, cleared inner rival and showed the way up the backstretch, was challenged midway through the far turn, lost command past the quarter pole and gave way.
